<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <head>No. 51.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Partridge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-11-10"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 10,
                                    1871</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 16, of the 29th of
                            September last, in relation to the passage of a “law of freedom” in
                            Brazil, has been received.</p>
                        <p>You will inform the government of Brazil that the President has <pb facs="0180" n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/> received with, much satisfaction
                            the intelligence of the passage of the law adverted to. Your course in
                            regard to the matter is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>